25|$|Gold rounds {{look exactly}} like gold coins {{but they have}} no {{currency}} value. They range in similar sizes as gold coins and come in 0.05 <b>troy</b> <b>ounce</b> {{all the way up to}} 1 <b>troy</b> <b>ounce.</b> Unlike gold coins, gold rounds have no additional metals added to them for durability purposes and do not have to be made by a government mint, which allows the gold rounds to have a lower overhead price as compared to gold coins. On the other hand, gold rounds are not as collectible as gold coins.|$|E
